column5: Where are you heading out of? What time? Might help others decide. Thanks,
Gull Lake, south of Minden, Saturday morning (if the ice is ok)  PM me your cell # Fidel
I just got a message that the ice on Opeongo is solid 24".....should be okay on Gull, unless there is current.
How did this go? I was thinking of you guys while I pounded back drinks sitting on the beach basking in the sun all day  Anyone show up?  How was the ice?  I'm jonesing for some fishing now.  S.
The day was this awesome!!! Great day, it was only Chris & I not another sole to be found on the lake, Fishing was awesome 9 Lakers total nothing of size but still fun.
Right on! I would have been there for sure if I wasnt away. Looks like mint weather!  S.
Fun day, good weather, not as good as the weather you had that day Shane, hopefully do it again next year
I'm going up and will check the ice on Friday. If people want to come up, the cost of being shuttled to the "spot" is 1 tall boy.  People with sleds or quads will receive 1 tall boy for helping out
Now that there's a deal !!!  But me and the girls gots some plans this weekend, otherwise it ain't that far really.  Have fun.
You receive zero tall boys Bunk
Friday looks to be my only day to get away. Weekend shift is keeping me pinned close to home. 2 tall boys is well worth a lift IMO. Yer letting them all off easy Chris.LOL
You also receive zero tall boys Brian
I'm in, you dig Guinness or Innis & Gunn?
Give him 4 Innis...in the pretty bottles lol
Oh boy, I have a feeling the June trip is going to be a riot, lol.
you come on Saturday I give you a tall boy Bill! Come on!  edit- Bring your 550. Hahaha
Kewley, you're a friend and welcome anytime
I might be able to come up on Friday. Saturday has been booked by the Family. CKewley is hitting the rivers on Friday. I have to ask the EIGHT BALL where to go.  Bain
Hahahaahah
One of these days Ill get out with ya Chris.  Its on my bucket list
not Friday, Saturday, family dinners come and go, spring ice in Halibuton trump that everytime
anytime Rick, us and little fisher may visit you some time soon too
Ha---tallboys---the redneck currency!!
come out Harold
If I wasnt going to be in cuba, Lori and I would be there with bells on. Think the ice will last another week?  S.
Shane has received a -2 tall boys
Its ok, I drink whiskey anyways.  I'll bring tallboys next time....... for all you girls...hahaha  Good luck!  S
Sooooooo tempting.
Even people I don't know are welcome. It's kinda like a last minute GTG and a farewell to the hard water season.
Sounds good to me!  Can I bring a friend?
If I hadn't already made plans for a full day at the girlfriends family in Lindsay... I'd be there. With the Bravo. BUT....  Sounds like a Blast though.
